Potatoes carries a lot of problems compared to grain crops.

The water content makes them difficult to store and transport properly,
so taxes would still have to paid in grain, and the long distance food trade
from the Baltic to the Cities in western Europe would still be in grain

Bread also lend itself better to preservation than food prepared from
potatoes so armies and navies would still be fueled by grain.

Potato crops are also more vulnerableto disease or insect attacks than
most grain crops. It makes quite a difference in a subsistence economy
if you lose almost 100% of a croip compared to 30%.

The biggest impact if potatoes were native to the old world would
imo have to wait until the infrastructure was developed enough
to handle the transportation and storage problems and to supply
areas with failed crops.

